{"questionId":"32995853","questionHtml":"<p>Use the result in part (d)(i) to deduce that the predicted number of trout at the start of any year will be greater than the predicted number at the start of the next year.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>D</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>D</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math> &nbsp; (because <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math> and so&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>150</mn><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>R1</strong></em> for responses such as:</p>\n<p>‘The difference is negative’.</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>150</mn><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>D</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>D</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mo>+</mo><mn>150</mn><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math></p>\n<p>Accept responses such as:</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>D</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>D</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; or&nbsp; ‘the difference is positive’ as long as <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>D</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>D</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></math> is referred to.</p>\n<p>Do not accept arguments based on specific numerical examples.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>therefore&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>D</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mo>&lt;</mo><msub><mi>D</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo>⇒</mo><msub><mi>D</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>D</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong><em>AG</em></strong></p>\n<p>(and hence the predicted number of trout at the start of any year will be greater than the predicted number at the start of the next year)</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"32995853","referenceCode":"24N.3.AHL.TZ0.1dii","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Use the result in part (d)(i) to deduce that the predicted number of trout at the start of any year will be greater than the predicted number at the start of the next year.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.6—Simple proof"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}